WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:03.171
Hey, good morning family, how are y'all doing today?

00:00:03.171 --> 00:00:05.740
Well, praise the Lord, we're excited to be here.

00:00:05.740 --> 00:00:15.580
I have some things on my heart to pray about, but I wanted to tell you all a testimony about a lady that was believing for a baby.

00:00:15.580 --> 00:00:24.760
She wasn't able to conceive, and so after my wife prayed for her, the Lord touched her body, and they're going to have their first baby, I believe—or another baby.

00:00:24.760 --> 00:00:29.765
I don't think it's their first baby, but they're going to have another child.

00:00:29.765 --> 00:00:32.239
And so, we're excited for them.

00:00:32.239 --> 00:00:40.860
Then right after that, we got another email from somebody getting ready to have a baby; they conceived all in the same time frame.

00:00:40.860 --> 00:00:43.180
I thought, well, maybe it was the same day we prayed.

00:00:44.239 --> 00:00:52.760
Isn't that amazing that God did that and that he is growing families in the kingdom of God?

00:00:52.760 --> 00:00:53.108
Hallelujah!

00:00:53.108 --> 00:00:59.800
And so, we're excited and we rejoice with all these people that are getting ready to have babies this next year.

00:00:59.800 --> 00:01:10.450
2025 is going to be a blessed year for some families—well, for everybody, but I'm just saying for these people who have been believing for children—so we're just excited and we just want to rejoice with you.

00:01:10.450 --> 00:01:16.220
If you have a healing testimony and the Lord's done something in your life through this channel, let us know.

00:01:17.255 --> 00:01:23.072
We're excited to see what the Lord is doing through everybody's lives, one soul at a time, one person at a time.

00:01:24.488 --> 00:01:29.691
We see it in demonstrations and manifestations of the glory; it's happening.

00:01:29.691 --> 00:01:35.984
And miracles, you know, signs and wonders in these last days, and we're expecting results.

00:01:35.984 --> 00:01:39.843
We're expecting when we pray, we give all the glory to the Lord.

00:01:39.843 --> 00:01:45.851
We give all of it because I'm telling you, nobody's even touching you, ladies and gentlemen, other than the Holy Spirit through this camera.

00:01:45.851 --> 00:01:51.306
And so it's exciting because I told you what the Lord told me.

00:01:51.306 --> 00:01:57.849
He said, 'In this last move, I'm going to do a lot of miracles and we're going to see signs and wonders.

00:01:57.849 --> 00:02:08.220
' And he said, 'Brandon, there's going to be like glory domes all over the place, and nobody's going to have to lay hands on you to receive it.

00:02:08.220 --> 00:02:13.724
You'll walk in there and the presence of the Lord will be so strong with the Shekinah glory.

00:02:13.959 --> 00:02:21.408
The weightiness of the glory will be in the atmosphere, and people will be healed because nobody's going to get the glory for it.

00:02:21.408 --> 00:02:22.840
It'll be all the glory to God.

00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:25.105
He's not going to share his glory with anybody.

00:02:25.105 --> 00:02:34.829
' And I'm excited to be a part of that because in this, we're just praying—just saying that prayer just like you would in your house—and the presence of the Lord goes in there and is delivering you.

00:02:34.829 --> 00:02:36.710
And I'm excited about that, y'all.

00:02:36.710 --> 00:02:39.702
This is exciting, and I believe this is just the beginning.

00:02:39.702 --> 00:02:59.349
The Lord told me, 'Brandon, I'm going to use this channel in an unusual way, a very unusual way, that we will see demonstrations and manifestations of the glory of God as we believe, as believers, for your unsaved loved ones, for deliverance, for healing, for all kinds of things.

00:02:59.349 --> 00:03:01.227
Whatever you may need, God has it.

00:03:01.227 --> 00:03:05.920
' And I just believe with all my heart today: today is your day for your miracle.

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:15.028
Why don't you believe God for what seemed to be impossible to become possible?

00:03:15.491 --> 00:03:18.353
All things are possible to him that believes.

00:03:18.599 --> 00:03:22.746
Today is your day for a supernatural visitation, manifestations of the glory.

00:03:22.746 --> 00:03:25.411
I want to tell you all about Billy Burke.

00:03:25.411 --> 00:03:27.069
I'm excited about Billy Burke.

00:03:27.069 --> 00:03:33.719
I've been watching Billy Burke a lot and the healings and things that are going on in his ministry.

00:03:33.719 --> 00:03:37.839
And you all keep telling me you're going and supporting him; I'm excited that you're supporting him.

00:03:39.171 --> 00:03:41.439
I want to tell you about a meeting that's coming.

00:03:41.439 --> 00:03:44.913
He's coming to Tulsa, Oklahoma, at the first part of December.

00:03:46.799 --> 00:04:00.200
In Tulsa, if you're in the area and you want to go and experience the miracles and the demonstrations and manifestations of the glory, he's going to be at Millennium Church, I believe it is, here in Oklahoma.

00:04:00.200 --> 00:04:02.280
And so, it's exciting times.

00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:04.410
I encourage you all to support him.

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:10.260
He goes all over the country; he has his itinerary online, and I just want everybody to support him.

00:04:11.069 --> 00:04:14.115
I saw the last meeting he had, there wasn't a lot of people there.

00:04:15.329 --> 00:04:16.773
He had it in Pittsburgh.

00:04:16.773 --> 00:04:34.624
And so, you know, I'd like for there to be standing room only for him in these meetings because I'm telling you all, I experienced the glory when I went, and I want people to really try to support this man and go see his ministry whenever he's in your area because I'm telling you, it will change your life.

00:04:34.624 --> 00:04:43.173
So if you go to Billy Burke and you're there and you see Billy Burke at the meeting and he brings you up on stage, tell him that I sent you because I think it would be cool.

00:04:44.559 --> 00:04:51.479
I think he's starting to know who I am a little bit by some of the people showing up at his meetings because he brought me up at his last service.

00:04:51.479 --> 00:04:56.291
Just say, 'Brandon sent me from the Last Days YouTube channel,' if you ever go.

00:05:03.256 --> 00:05:03.488
So that'll bless me.

00:05:11.231 --> 00:05:13.045
And I don't even personally know this man; all I know is when I went to his service and he prayed for me, my life will never be the same.

00:05:19.943 --> 00:05:26.220
And so, if the presence of the Lord would do that for me at his meeting, I believe he'll do it for you at the meeting also.

00:05:28.627 --> 00:05:33.430
And so, another thing: Sister Billie Brim is having a conference in February at Glorious Church with Rick Renner.

00:05:33.430 --> 00:05:40.960
And she is going to be teaching on the end times and the Rapture of the church—where we are in the end times.

00:05:40.960 --> 00:05:47.183
And this has never been done before with her and Rick Renner.

00:05:47.183 --> 00:06:03.250
They're going to be doing like a table talk where they're going to be talking about the end times for a whole week, everything from where we are in the tribulation, where we'll go, and the Thousand-Year Reign, all kinds of stuff.

00:06:03.250 --> 00:06:04.310
Really cool eschatology.

00:06:04.310 --> 00:06:11.360
I'm sure they'll talk about all—I mean, really, it will be full of knowledge, full of information.

00:06:15.164 --> 00:06:18.549
You know, Rick Renner is a Bible scholar and he studies out the Greek and is brilliant; he has a brilliant mind when it comes to the word of God.

00:06:18.549 --> 00:06:22.500
And I am looking forward to it.

00:06:32.793 --> 00:06:33.056
But I wanted to tell you all, you can put it on your calendar that it's going to be in February, and they're coming to the Glorious Church Fellowship.

00:06:45.769 --> 00:06:51.045
So if you're interested in going to that, I'm sure it would bless you.

00:06:51.714 --> 00:06:54.251
It would be a Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, or something like that.

00:06:56.646 --> 00:06:59.707
I don't remember exactly the dates, but I will update you again.

00:07:02.262 --> 00:07:08.920
You can either call Glorious Church or look at their website and be able to see when they're having this meeting, but I believe it's the first week of February.

00:07:08.920 --> 00:07:18.640
So I just want to encourage you all to support that and hopefully it'll bless you because I believe it's going to bless us.

00:07:18.640 --> 00:07:20.439
Aren't you excited about Diana?

00:07:20.439 --> 00:07:21.740
Yes, it's exciting times.

00:07:21.740 --> 00:07:36.159
We love hearing about eschatology and about end-time teaching, especially from Rick, and then when you put Billie together with Rick and the Greek and all that, it's like, oh my gosh, this is going to be phenomenal.

00:07:43.130 --> 00:07:43.420
So I just want to encourage you all today to believe God for big.

00:07:55.244 --> 00:08:06.822
I know people get discouraged, I know we get weary in well-doing, but I want you to hold up your head today and know that Jesus loves you even in the midst of the storms of life—even whenever it seems like all things are coming against you and the waves of life are knocking you down.

00:08:11.095 --> 00:08:11.380
I just want you to keep your head up.

00:08:11.380 --> 00:08:22.720
I've been there, and there are days that I feel like I don't want to—I'm like, 'How can I even come out and do another video today?

00:08:32.175 --> 00:08:32.490
I'm so tired.

00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:42.853
' But you know, you just keep on keeping on even when things seem to be at their worst.

00:08:46.445 --> 00:08:50.827
You know, I see all these bugs and all this stuff flying around me, I'm not used to all this, I get distracted.

00:08:50.827 --> 00:08:53.244
It's like, 'There's a bug, there's a bug!

00:08:53.244 --> 00:08:59.600
' But whenever things seem to be at their hardest, that's whenever the light comes out strongest.

00:08:59.600 --> 00:09:03.244
I believe with all my heart it's darkest before dawn.

00:09:03.244 --> 00:09:06.640
I just want to encourage you all to keep on keeping on.

00:09:06.640 --> 00:09:10.920
Don't give up whenever you're believing for your miracle.

00:09:10.920 --> 00:09:15.940
I know there's some days that seem like it's never going to happen.

00:09:24.639 --> 00:09:24.920
You may feel that way in your natural, like, 'Oh, do I have to go through another day of this?

00:09:24.920 --> 00:09:29.399
' But I'm telling you, in due season's coming.

00:09:40.800 --> 00:09:41.173
In due season's coming.

00:09:41.173 --> 00:09:55.920
You have to keep on keeping on, fighting the good fight of faith, regardless if you're having a hard time in your marriage, you may be having a hard time with your kids, or you may be having a hard time with your job.

00:09:59.707 --> 00:10:03.530
And you may think, 'Man, I can't go in there another day and serve and work at this place anymore.

00:10:03.530 --> 00:10:07.510
God, are you going to open another door for me for another great job?

00:10:07.510 --> 00:10:24.751
' The job is a big deal for a lot of people because you spend eight hours a day there, sometimes more, every single day, five days a week, sometimes six days a week, working your tail end off trying to make a living, trying to do things to supply for your families.

00:10:24.751 --> 00:10:29.860
There's men out there that are working full-time, two jobs, three jobs, who knows?

00:10:41.844 --> 00:10:42.329
And you get to the point where you get weary in well-doing, where you get to the holiday times and you're thinking, 'How am I going to buy Christmas for my kids?

00:10:42.329 --> 00:10:47.400
How am I going to buy Thanksgiving dinner for my family?

00:10:47.400 --> 00:10:55.431
' But I'm telling you, God said in his word that he would supply all your needs according to his riches in glory by Christ Jesus.

00:10:57.279 --> 00:11:08.631
And regardless of your—and I always told myself whenever we didn't have much, we were down at the bottom of the barrel, thinking, 'Lord, how are we going to do this?

00:11:08.631 --> 00:11:12.000
' And the Lord always provided a way.

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:21.360
He always takes care of his beloved, and I believe with all my heart he'll take care of you.

00:11:21.360 --> 00:11:23.691
He's no respecter of persons.

00:11:25.377 --> 00:11:38.739
But there would be times whenever we were down to our last ten cents, it seemed like we didn't have anything, and we were like, 'Oh man, what are we going to do?

00:11:38.739 --> 00:11:39.839
' Remember, Die?

00:11:39.839 --> 00:11:42.354
It was terrible, and the Lord always provided.

00:11:42.354 --> 00:11:48.030
It wasn't always the best of what we thought we needed, but we got through.

00:11:52.011 --> 00:11:55.239
And so I'm trying to encourage you all to know that God's going to take care of you.

00:11:55.239 --> 00:12:07.072
Believing for a creative idea—I know a lot of people don't want to hear this, but there's a lot of people that are struggling because we get the emails, and I know that God is a provider.

00:12:07.072 --> 00:12:08.440
God is El Elyon, the Most High.

00:12:08.440 --> 00:12:10.030
He is a Jehovah Jireh.

00:12:10.030 --> 00:12:20.148
He will provide for you, he will heal you, he will deliver you, and all you have to do is reach out in simple faith.

00:12:20.148 --> 00:12:24.959
Abraham—it says in the word—Abraham staggered not at the promise of God through unbelief.

00:12:24.959 --> 00:12:36.914
He knew in the deadness of her womb, she was old, there was no life in that womb to bring forth a new child, but the Lord saw to it to bring him forth, Isaac.

00:12:47.691 --> 00:12:47.937
And I believe with all my heart that there's Isaacs coming, not just in babies, but in every area of your life.

00:12:47.937 --> 00:12:52.340
Isaacs—there's blessings, there's increase, there's new jobs, there's multiplication, there's promotions.

00:12:52.340 --> 00:12:57.079
Whatever you may need, I believe with all my heart God has your Isaac.

00:12:57.079 --> 00:13:01.109
Does that make sense what I'm trying to say, ladies and gentlemen?

00:13:09.089 --> 00:13:23.920
I'm trying to tell you to believe God and stagger not at the promises that God said he would supply for all your needs according to riches and glory, that he would heal you by his stripes, that he would deliver you, and that with long life he would satisfy you and show you his salvation—Psalms 91—and that he would give you peace in your homes.

00:13:25.819 --> 00:13:41.075
You don't have to go home tonight and be tormented and go, 'Well, you know, we're going to go home, my wife and I are going to fight probably all night and I'll sleep in the other room, won't have anybody to be with because our marriage is just terrible.

00:13:41.075 --> 00:13:43.691
' Remember, you have what you say.

00:13:55.514 --> 00:13:55.817
The Bible says call those things that be not as though they were, and you have to speak to your circumstances and say, 'My marriage is good.

00:13:55.817 --> 00:14:12.000
' Even whenever Diana and I were having a hard time when Megan was first diagnosed, there were days, because of how much pressure it was having a special needs child, that I was like, 'Man, I don't want to do this anymore.

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:30.968
' It wasn't because of Diana; it was because the circumstances were making—I've always loved Diana, we've had a really good friendship and a good marriage, but there's been times whenever there's been pressure from circumstances of life that really try to put pressure on the marriage and put pressure on the finances, pressure on things that you go, 'I don't want to do this anymore.

00:14:30.968 --> 00:14:35.781
' And you've got to have that inside, that bulldog on a bone, saying, 'I will keep doing this.

00:14:35.781 --> 00:14:39.067
I signed up for this, I'm going to do this.

00:14:44.258 --> 00:14:47.390
I made a covenant with her, I made a covenant with him, and we're going to walk through the valley and we're going to make this happen.

00:14:47.390 --> 00:14:57.396
We're not quitters, we're fighters, and we're doers of the word, regardless of how hard life throws these curveballs and fastballs at you.

00:14:57.396 --> 00:15:01.080
' You've got to keep on keeping on and know that we're not quitters.

00:15:01.080 --> 00:15:04.234
We have to be the army, and we have to be the backbone.

00:15:04.566 --> 00:15:11.560
And when things are thrown at us the hardest, that's whenever you keep saying the strongest, 'Nope, I'm going to keep making this marriage work.

00:15:11.560 --> 00:15:15.698
Nope, I'm going to fight and I'm going to believe for my child's healing.

00:15:15.698 --> 00:15:20.440
No, I'm going to believe for a better job, I'm going to believe God for a creative idea.

00:15:20.440 --> 00:15:23.667
' And it didn't even come through me, ladies and gentlemen.

00:15:26.940 --> 00:15:30.782
The idea to do eBay, the idea to do Poshmark, the ideas to sell things on Facebook Marketplace—that came from the Holy Spirit and my wife.

00:15:30.782 --> 00:15:36.359
So you think a lot of times, 'Well, it's going to have to come through the man.

00:15:36.359 --> 00:15:39.992
' No, listen to your wife and what she has to say.

00:15:39.992 --> 00:15:46.577
She may have a creative idea that might get you out of the hole, too.

00:15:46.577 --> 00:15:53.785
Don't always try to be the one who says, 'Well, I'm the head, I'm going to get this through.

00:15:53.785 --> 00:16:03.733
' No, it came through my sweet wife, and whenever she said it, I didn't even believe it.

00:16:03.733 --> 00:16:09.164
I'd say, 'Is this the way God wants to do this for our family?

00:16:09.164 --> 00:16:17.700
' because pride comes in as a man and you think, 'Well, I'm not going to listen to that.

00:16:17.700 --> 00:16:23.364
' And I just had to just say, 'Listen, buddy, you better shut your mouth.

00:16:23.364 --> 00:16:25.490
' You know what I'm saying?

00:16:25.490 --> 00:16:42.188
I'm just saying, there is a lot of times that the Lord will use unexpected ways, and it doesn't have to be how you think it's going to happen because you try to box God in, you try to limit God, you try to tell him, 'This is how you're going to operate in our life.

00:16:42.188 --> 00:16:46.769
' And God is exceedingly abundantly above all that you dare ask or think.

00:16:46.769 --> 00:16:52.893
God is not going to operate in your peanut brain in how he's going to get it to you.

00:17:01.865 --> 00:17:02.240
It comes through—like I told you all, I had a man—I was just cleaning the floors of the church, not expecting it at all.

00:17:02.650 --> 00:17:12.083
It was a big Christmas program that we were doing at the church and I was just in there cleaning, and we didn't have any Christmas presents for the kids or anything.

00:17:12.083 --> 00:17:18.804
We wanted to get the gifts for the family and we were like, 'Man, Lord,' and we were down to nothing.

00:17:18.804 --> 00:17:26.839
And this man out of nowhere walks up to me—his name was Tim—and he walked up to me and he said, 'The Lord told me to give you this $1,000.

00:17:26.839 --> 00:17:30.933
' It would have seemed like it was a million dollars, ladies and gentlemen, for where we were.

00:17:30.933 --> 00:17:34.569
$1,000—that was like—because I only made like eight bucks an hour.

00:17:42.240 --> 00:17:42.496
So when you get $1,000 on janitor's wages, you go, 'My God.

00:17:42.496 --> 00:17:44.676
' You know, the Lord came through.

00:17:44.907 --> 00:17:53.295
And I remember sitting there when he walked away, I went outside and I called Diana and I said, 'Babe, the Lord just provided our Christmas,' and she just wept on the phone with me.

00:18:02.147 --> 00:18:02.333
We both wept because God came through.

00:18:02.893 --> 00:18:05.742
And it's not just one time he's done that.

00:18:05.742 --> 00:18:09.693
If he did it once, he'll do it again.

00:18:15.140 --> 00:18:16.760
And that's where we believe him all the time, even today for it, ladies and gentlemen.

00:18:16.760 --> 00:18:21.070
I don't always have my stuff together.

00:18:21.070 --> 00:18:27.671
I may—you may think I do, and it may seem like I do on this camera, but we believe God for stuff all the time.

00:18:27.671 --> 00:18:28.729
We're still believing him for stuff.

00:18:29.690 --> 00:18:35.508
You say, 'Well, Brandon, what are you doing with your faith right now?

00:18:35.508 --> 00:18:49.940
' I'm believing for things that if I told you what I was believing for, it would freak you out because of things the Lord has told me that we're going to have to do for this ministry.

00:18:53.204 --> 00:18:58.425
But we keep on, and we know that it is not by our might, not by my power, but by the spirit, says the Lord.

00:18:58.425 --> 00:19:07.789
Regardless of how big it is, sometimes the mountain seems so big that you can't climb it and you go, 'How in the world am I going to get up there?

00:19:07.789 --> 00:19:10.920
' other than just say, 'Lord, I trust you.

00:19:12.320 --> 00:19:16.620
You said it, and now you're going to bring it to pass.

00:19:16.620 --> 00:19:22.300
You told us to do it, now you're going to bring it to pass.

00:19:22.300 --> 00:19:26.600
I'm not going to be moved by what I see.

00:19:26.600 --> 00:19:30.400
I'm not moved by what I feel.

00:19:30.400 --> 00:19:35.008
' If you don't bring it, I'm not going to worry about it.

00:19:35.995 --> 00:19:36.159
It's your bill, Lord.

00:19:40.030 --> 00:19:42.724
I used to get so upset about it, I used to have anxiety about it, and it was bad.

00:19:42.724 --> 00:19:54.600
For a long time, I told Die, I said, 'If I could just get a couple months extra in the bank so I don't stress out about these finances all the time—about your electric, your water, your gas, and your car payment.

00:19:54.600 --> 00:20:04.400
' Because there was a time whenever they repoed our car; they came and took it, and we would sit there and just watch it go down the street.

00:20:04.400 --> 00:20:05.936
It sucks—it's just being real.

00:20:15.860 --> 00:20:16.700
And you get to that point where you get really discouraged when they come and get your broke-down Honda with 200,000 miles on it, and you're going, 'What gives?

00:20:16.700 --> 00:20:19.766
' And then you keep believing.

00:20:19.766 --> 00:20:22.410
That's what I'm trying to tell y'all.

00:20:22.410 --> 00:20:23.264
We've been there.

00:20:23.264 --> 00:20:33.880
We know what it's like to be at the bottom of the barrel and the barrel be on top of you, like Brother Hagin used to say.

00:20:33.880 --> 00:20:36.969
But God, who is rich in mercy.

00:20:36.969 --> 00:20:40.777
So I hope this encourages you today that you're not alone.

00:20:42.080 --> 00:20:51.120
You may think you're alone, you may think God's not hearing you, you may think he's abandoned us, 'We don't even have enough for some Spam and some peanut butter and jelly.

00:20:51.120 --> 00:21:11.110
' But I'm telling you, if you keep on being faithful, you keep speaking to your circumstances, if you keep calling those things that be not as though they were, you keep speaking to your marriage—'My marriage is good, my marriage is whole, my marriage is healthy'—because what you say out of your mouth is what you're going to have tomorrow.

00:21:11.110 --> 00:21:16.080
What you said out of your mouth today is what you lived yesterday.

00:21:16.080 --> 00:21:18.269
Life is a series of choices.

00:21:18.269 --> 00:21:25.731
We were talking about it even yesterday; I said, 'Isn't it amazing, it's the small decisions that make the big decision.

00:21:25.731 --> 00:21:29.366
' We're always looking for the big thing.

00:21:29.366 --> 00:21:38.704
For me, struggling with my weight, eating wrong foods, bad foods during the day—I'll pick up something and put it in my mouth, it's something so small and yet it tries to ruin me.

00:21:38.704 --> 00:21:57.760
It's something that I deal with, and you get that stress and you go, 'Man, I've got to have that piece of candy,' and I put it in my mouth and I didn't even realize I did it because it's just something that I've dealt with.

00:22:11.919 --> 00:22:12.169
And I try so hard to turn it around.

00:22:16.853 --> 00:22:17.040
I say, 'Tomorrow, the diet starts tomorrow.

